79  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void setPos(difference_type new_pos) noexcept
80  {
81  size_type front_size = mgr->d_buckets.front()->size;
82  size_type bindex = (new_pos + (mgr->d_bucket_size - front_size)) >> mgr->d_bucket_size_bits;
83  size_type index_in_bucket = (new_pos - (new_pos < (difference_type)front_size ? 0 : front_size)) & mgr->d_bucket_size1;
84 
85  bucket = mgr->d_buckets.data() + bindex;
86 
87  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bindex == mgr->d_buckets.size())) {
88  // end iterator
89  ptr = begin_ptr = first_stop = 0;
90  }
91  else {
92 
93  ptr = (cbuffer_pos )(&(*bucket)->at((cbuffer_pos)index_in_bucket) - (*bucket)->buffer());
94  begin_ptr = (*bucket)->begin_index();
95  first_stop = (ptr < begin_ptr) ? (*bucket)->second_stop() : (*bucket)->first_stop();
96  }

104  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void go_next() noexcept
105  {
106  const cbuffer_pos sstop = (*bucket)->second_stop();
107  if (first_stop == sstop)
108  {
109  bucket++;
110  if (pos != (difference_type)mgr->size()) {
111  begin_ptr = ptr = (*bucket)->begin_index();
112  first_stop = (*bucket)->first_stop();
113  }
114  else
115  ptr = begin_ptr = first_stop = 0;
116  }
117  else {
118  first_stop = sstop;
119  ptr = 0;
120  }
121  }
122  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void go_prev() noexcept
123  {
124  if (ptr == begin_ptr - 1)
125  {
126  bucket--;
127  ptr = (cbuffer_pos)((*bucket)->last_ptr() - (*bucket)->buffer());
128  begin_ptr = (*bucket)->begin_index();
129  first_stop = (*bucket)->second_stop();
130  }
131  else if (ptr == -1) {
132  first_stop = (*bucket)->first_stop();
133  ptr = (*bucket)->max_size1;
134  }
135  }

319  // Circular buffer class used internally by tiered_vector
320  // Actuall data are located in the same memory block and starts at start_data_T
321  template<class T, class Allocator>
322  struct CircularBuffer : BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>
323  {
324  static const size_t size_T = sizeof(T);
325  static const size_t size_BCB = sizeof(BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>);
326  static const size_t start_data_T = (size_BCB > size_T) ?
327  (size_BCB / size_T + ((size_BCB % size_T) != 0u ? 1 : 0)) :
328  1;
329  static const size_t start_data = start_data_T * sizeof(T);
330  static const bool relocatable = is_relocatable<T>::value && (sizeof(T) >= sizeof(size_t));
331 
332  using BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>::size;
333  using BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>::max_size1;
334  using BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>::max_size_;
335  using BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>::begin;
336 
337  // Initialize from a maximum size
338  CircularBuffer(cbuffer_pos max_size) noexcept
339  :BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>(max_size) {
340  //initialize empty buffer
341  }
342  // Initialize from a maximum size and a default value.
343  // This will set the buffer size to its maximum.
344  CircularBuffer(cbuffer_pos max_size, const T& val, Allocator& /*unused*/)
345  :BaseCircularBuffer<T, Allocator>(max_size) {
346  size = max_size;
347  //initialize full buffer
348  cbuffer_pos i = 0;
349  try {
350  for (; i < max_size; ++i)
351  construct_ptr(buffer() + i, val);
352  }
353  catch (...) {
354  for (cbuffer_pos j = 0; j < i; ++j)
355  destroy_ptr(buffer() + j);
356  size = 0;
357  throw;
358  }
359  }
360 
361  // Destroy all values within buffer
362  void destroy(Allocator& /*unused*/) noexcept {
363  if (!std::is_trivially_destructible<T>::value) {
364  for (cbuffer_pos i = 0; i < size; ++i)
365  destroy_ptr(&(*this)[i]);
366  }
367  }
368 
369  //Disable copy
370  CircularBuffer(const CircularBuffer& other) = delete;
371  auto operator=(const CircularBuffer& other) -> CircularBuffer& = delete;

373  //Raw buffer access
374  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto buffer() noexcept -> T* { return (T*)((char*)this + start_data); }
375  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto buffer() const noexcept -> const T* { return (const T*)((char*)this + start_data); }
376 
377  //Pointer on the first data
378  auto begin_ptr() noexcept -> T* { return buffer() + ((begin)&max_size1); }
379  auto begin_ptr() const noexcept -> const T* { return buffer() + ((begin)&max_size1); }
380  //Pointer on the last data
381  auto last_ptr() noexcept -> T* { return (buffer() + ((begin + size - 1) & max_size1)); }
382  auto last_ptr() const noexcept -> const T* { return (buffer() + ((begin + size - 1) & max_size1)); }
383  //Index of the first data
384  auto begin_index() const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos { return (begin)&max_size1; }
385  // Index of the first stop (either at size or max size)
386  auto first_stop() const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos {
387  cbuffer_pos p = begin_index();
388  return (p + size) > max_size() ? (max_size()) : (p + size);
389  }
390  // Index of the second stop (either at size or max size)
391  auto second_stop() const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos {
392  cbuffer_pos p = begin_index();
393  return (p + size) > max_size() ? (((p + size) & max_size1)) : (p + size);
394  }
395  //Buffer maximum size
396  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto max_size() const noexcept -> cbuffer_pos {
397  return max_size_;
398  }
399  //Check if full
400  auto isFull() const noexcept -> bool { return size == max_size(); }
401  //Element access.

433  // Resize buffer
434  void resize(cbuffer_pos s, Allocator& /*unused*/) {
435  if (s < size) {
436  if (!std::is_trivially_destructible<T>::value) {
437  for (cbuffer_pos i = s; i < size; ++i)
438  destroy_ptr(&(*this)[i]);
439  }
440  }
441  else if (s > size) {
442  cbuffer_pos i = size;
443  // Make sure to destroy constructed values in case of exception
444  try {
445  for (; i < s; ++i)
446  construct_ptr(&(*this)[i]);
447  }
448  catch (...) {
449  for (cbuffer_pos j = size; j < i; ++j)
450  destroy_ptr(&(*this)[j]);
451  throw;
452  }
453  }
454  size = s;
455  }

461  }
462  }

464  cbuffer_pos i = size;

529  // Pushing front while poping back value for relocatable types
530  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void push_front_pop_back_use_relocatable(T& inout) noexcept {
531  typename std::aligned_storage<sizeof(T), alignof(T)>::type tmp;
532  memcpy((void*)(&tmp), &back(), sizeof(T));
533  if (--begin < 0) begin = max_size1;
534  memcpy((void*)(buffer() + begin), &inout, sizeof(T));
535  memcpy((void*)(&inout), &tmp, sizeof(T));
536  }
537  // Pushing front while poping back value for relocatable types, except arithmetic ones
538  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void push_front_pop_back_relocatable(T& inout)noexcept(std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<T>::value) {
539  if (std::is_arithmetic<T>::value)
540  inout = std::move(push_front_pop_back(std::move(inout)));
541  else
542  push_front_pop_back_use_relocatable(inout);
543  }

545  // Might throw, but leave the buffer in a valid state
546  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto push_front_pop_back(T&& value) noexcept(std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<T>::value) -> T {
547  // Only works for filled array
548  T res = std::move(back());

554  // Pushing front while poping back for relocatable types
555  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void push_back_pop_front_use_relocatable(T& inout) noexcept {
556  typename std::aligned_storage<sizeof(T), alignof(T)>::type tmp;
557  memcpy((void*)(&tmp), &front(), sizeof(T));

569  // Pushing front while poping back
570  // Might throw, but leave the buffer in a valid state since it is already full
571  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE auto push_back_pop_front(T&& value) noexcept(std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<T>::value) -> T {
572  // Only works for filled array
573  T res = std::move(front());
574  begin = (begin + 1) & (max_size1);
575  (*this)[size - 1] = std::move(value);
576  return (res);
577  }

583  }
584  void pop_front(Allocator& /*unused*/) {
585  destroy_ptr(buffer() + begin);
586  begin = (begin + 1) & (max_size1);
587  --size;
588  }

620  // Move buffer content toward the right by 1 element
621  // Might throw
622  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void move_right_1(int pos) noexcept(std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<T>::value || relocatable)
623  {
624  //starting from pos, move elements toward the end
625  T* ptr1 = &at(size - 1);
626  T* stop = &at(pos);
627  if (stop > ptr1)
628  stop = buffer();
629 
630  if (!relocatable) {
631  while (ptr1 > stop) {
632  ptr1[0] = std::move(ptr1[-1]);
633  --ptr1;
634  }
635  }
636  else {
637  memmove((void*)(stop + 1), (void*)stop, (ptr1 - stop) * sizeof(T)); ptr1 = stop;
638  }
639 
640  if (ptr1 != &at(pos)) {
641  if (!relocatable)
642  *ptr1 = std::move(*(buffer() + max_size1));
643  else
644  memcpy((void*)ptr1, (void*)(buffer() + max_size1), sizeof(T));
645  ptr1 = (buffer() + max_size1);
646  stop = &at(pos);
647  if (!relocatable) {
648  while (ptr1 > stop) {
649  ptr1[0] = std::move(ptr1[-1]);
650  --ptr1;
651  }
652  }
653  else {
654  memmove((void*)(stop + 1), (void*)stop, (ptr1 - stop) * sizeof(T));
655  }
656  }
657  }
658  // Move buffer content toward the left by 1 element
659  // Might throw
660  SEQ_ALWAYS_INLINE void move_left_1(int pos) noexcept(std::is_nothrow_move_assignable<T>::value || relocatable)
661  {
662  //starting from pos, move elements toward the beginning
663  T* ptr1 = &at(0);
664  //T* ptr2 = ptr1 + 1;
665  T* stop = buffer() + ((begin + pos - 1) & max_size1);//&at(pos);
666  if (stop < ptr1)
667  stop = buffer() + max_size1;
668  if (!relocatable) {
669  while (ptr1 < stop) {
670  *ptr1 = std::move(ptr1[1]);
671  ++ptr1;
672  }
673  }
674  else {
675  memmove((void*)ptr1, (void*)(ptr1 + 1), (stop - ptr1) * sizeof(T)); ptr1 = stop;
676  }
677  if (ptr1 != buffer() + ((begin + pos - 1) & max_size1)) {
678  if (!relocatable)
679  *ptr1 = std::move(*(buffer()));
680  else
681  memcpy((void*)ptr1, (void*)buffer(), sizeof(T));
682  ptr1 = buffer();
683  stop = &at(pos - 1);
684  if (!relocatable) {
685  while (ptr1 < stop) {
686  *ptr1 = std::move(ptr1[1]);
687  ++ptr1;
688  }
689  }
690  else {
691  memmove((void*)ptr1, (void*)(ptr1 + 1), (stop - ptr1) * sizeof(T));
692  }
693  }
694  }

697  // Might throw
698  SEQ_NOINLINE(void) move_right(Allocator& /*unused*/, cbuffer_pos pos)
699  {
700  if (!relocatable)
701  construct_ptr(&(*this)[size]);
702  //move elems after pos
703  ++size;
704  // Might throw, fine since no more values are constructed/destructed
705  move_right_1(pos);
706  // Non optimized way:
707  //for (cbuffer_pos i = size - 1; i > pos; --i)
708  // (*this)[i] = std::move((*this)[i - 1]);
709  }
710  SEQ_NOINLINE(void) move_left(Allocator& /*unused*/, cbuffer_pos pos)
711  {
712  if (!relocatable)
713  construct_ptr(&(*this)[begin ? -1 : max_size1]);
714  //move elems before pos
715  if (--begin < 0) begin = max_size1;
716  ++size;
717  // Might throw, fine since no more values are constructed/destructed
718  move_left_1(pos + 1);
719  // Non optimized way:
720  //for (cbuffer_pos i = 0; i < pos -1; ++i)
721  // (*this)[i] = std::move((*this)[i + 1]);
722  }

724  // Insert value at given position. Only works if the buffer is not full.
725  template <class... Args>
726  auto emplace(Allocator& allocator, cbuffer_pos pos, Args&&... args) -> T*
727  {
728  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(size != max_size_, "cannot insert in a full circular buffer");
729  if (pos > size / 2) {
730  move_right(allocator, pos);
731  }
732  else {
733  move_left(allocator, pos);
734  }
735 
736  T* res = &(*this)[pos];
737  if (relocatable) {
738  try {
739  construct_ptr(res, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
740  }
741  catch (...) {
742  //No choice but to destroy all values after pos and reduce the size in order to leave the buffer in a valid state
743  for (int i = pos + 1; i < size; ++i)
744  destroy_ptr(&(*this)[i]);
745  size = pos;
746  throw;
747  }
748  }
749  else {
750  // For non relocatable types, use move assignment to provide basic exception guarantee
751  *res = T(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
752  }
753 
754  return res;
755  }
756 
757  // Insert value at given position. Only works if the buffer is not full.
758  auto insert(Allocator& allocator, cbuffer_pos pos, const T& value) -> T* {
759  return emplace(allocator, pos, value);
760  }
761  auto insert(Allocator& allocator, cbuffer_pos pos, T&& value) -> T* {
762  return emplace(allocator, pos, std::move(value));
763  }

1044  //Bucket allocator/deallocator class.
1045  //This version uses the default allocator object passed to the tiered_vector (default).
1046  template<class T, class Allocator>
1047  struct SmallBucketAllocator
1048  {
1049  using BucketType = CircularBuffer<T, Allocator>;
1050  template< class U>
1051  using RebindAlloc = typename std::allocator_traits<Allocator>::template rebind_alloc<U>;
1052  static constexpr int SizeofHeader = BucketType::start_data_T;
1053  Allocator allocator;
1054  SmallBucketAllocator(const Allocator& al) noexcept :allocator(al) {}
1055  SmallBucketAllocator(Allocator&& al) noexcept :allocator(std::move(al)) {}

1057  SmallBucketAllocator(SmallBucketAllocator&& other, const Allocator& al) noexcept : allocator(al) {}
1058  auto operator=(SmallBucketAllocator&& other) noexcept -> SmallBucketAllocator& {
1059  allocator = (std::move(other.allocator));
1060  return *this;
1061  }

1063  BucketType* res = (BucketType*)allocator.allocate(SizeofHeader + max_size);
1064  RebindAlloc<BucketType> alloc = allocator;
1065  // Never throw
1066  construct_ptr(res, max_size);
1067  return res;
1068  }

1070  BucketType* res = (BucketType*)allocator.allocate(SizeofHeader + max_size);
1071  RebindAlloc<BucketType> alloc = allocator;
1072  // Might throw
1073  try {
1074  construct_ptr(res, max_size, val, allocator);
1075  }
1076  catch (...) {
1077  allocator.deallocate((T*)res, SizeofHeader + max_size);
1078  throw;
1079  }
1080  return res;
1081  }

1083  buff->destroy(allocator);
1084  allocator.deallocate((T*)buff, SizeofHeader + buff->max_size());
1085  }

1297  if (size == (size_type)-1)
1298  full_size = other.d_size;
1299  else if (size > other.d_size)
1300  full_size = other.d_size;
1301

1303  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(start + full_size <= other.size(), "invalid end position");
1304 
1305  // Get new bucket count
1306  size_type bucket_count = full_size / new_bucket_size + (full_size % new_bucket_size ? 1 : 0);
1307

1309  d_ballocator.init(bucket_count, new_bucket_size);
1310

1312  // There is only one bucket: just fill front buffer
1313  // Might throw, fine

1317  }
1318  }
1319  else {
1320

1322  size_type end_pos = start + full_size;
1323

1328  T* ptr = current->buffer();
1329

1332  if (end > end_pos)
1333  end = end_pos;
1334

1336  Allocator al = get_allocator();

1338  other.for_each(pos, end, [&](const T& v) {construct_ptr(ptr++, v); });
1339  }
1340  catch (...) {

1343  for (T* p = current->buffer(); p != ptr; ++p)
1344  destroy_ptr(p);
1345  this->remove_back_bucket();
1346  throw;
1347  }

1349  pos += copied;
1350  d_size += copied;

1354  current->size = (cbuffer_pos)copied;
1355  current->resize(current->size, get_allocator());
1356  }
1357  else {
1358  // Fill front buffer
1359  current->grow_front((cbuffer_pos)copied);
1360  }
1361  }
1362  }
1363

1365  update_all_back_values();
1366 
1367  }

1511  // For each function, faster than using iterators
1512  template<class Functor>
1513  auto for_each(size_type start, size_type end, Functor fun) const -> Functor
1514  {
1515  size_type remaining = end - start;
1516  size_type bindex = bucket_index(start);
1517  size_type pos = (size_type)bucket_pos(start);
1518 
1519  while (remaining) {
1520  const BucketType* cur = d_buckets[bindex].bucket;
1521 
1522  size_type offset = cur->begin + pos;
1523  const T* b_end = cur->buffer() + cur->max_size();
1524  const T* _start = cur->buffer() + offset;
1525  if (_start > b_end)
1526  _start = cur->buffer() + (_start - b_end);
1527  size_type to_copy = std::min(remaining, (size_type)cur->size - pos );
1528  const T* _send = _start + to_copy;
1529  const T* _end = (_send > b_end) ? b_end : _send;
1530  while (_start < _end)
1531  fun(*_start++);
1532 
1533  if (_send > b_end) {
1534  _start = cur->buffer();
1535  _end = _start + to_copy - (cur->max_size() - offset);
1536  while (_start < _end)
1537  fun(*_start++);
1538  }
1539  remaining -= to_copy;
1540  pos = 0;
1541  ++bindex;
1542  }
1543  return fun;
1544  }

1715  auto emplace_back(Args&&... args) -> T& {
1716  // All functions might throw, fine (strong guarantee)
1717  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(d_buckets.empty()))
1718  create_back_bucket();
1719  BucketType* bucket = d_buckets.back().bucket;
1720  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bucket->size == d_bucket_size)) {
1721  bucket = create_back_bucket();
1722  }
1723  T* ptr = bucket->push_back(get_allocator(), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1724  if(StoreBackValues) d_buckets.back().update();
1725  d_size++;
1726  return *ptr;
1727  }

1757  // Insertion in the case where d_buckets.size() == 1
1758  template< class... Args >
1759  auto insert_one_bucket(size_type bucket_index, int index, Args&&... args) -> T*
1760  {
1761  T* res = NULL;
1762  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(bucket_index == 0, "Corrupted tiered_vector");
1763  if (d_buckets[0]->isFull()) {
1764 
1765  // All functions might throw, fine
1766  res = create_back_bucket()->push_back(get_allocator(), std::move(d_buckets[0]->insert_pop_back(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...)));
1767  if (StoreBackValues) {
1768  d_buckets.back().update();
1769  d_buckets[0].update();
1770  }
1771  }
1772  else {
1773  // Might throw, fine
1774  res = d_buckets[0].bucket->emplace(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...);

1779  template< class... Args >
1780  auto insert_left(size_type pos, size_type bucket_index, int index, Args&&... args) -> T*
1781  {
1782  T* res = NULL;
1783  //bucket is on the left side
1784  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(index == 0)) {
1785  --bucket_index; //we work on the previous bucket
1786  index = bucket(bucket_index)->size;
1787  }
1788  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bucket(bucket_index)->size < d_bucket_size)) {
1789  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(bucket_index == 0, "Corrupted tiered_vector structure");
1790  // We insert into the first bucket which is not full
1791  // Might throw, fine
1792  res = bucket(bucket_index)->emplace(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1793  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bucket_index].update();
1794  }
1795  else if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(bucket_index == 0)) {
1796  //insert into full first bucket
1797  // Might throw, fine

1799  try {
1800  res = create_front_bucket()->push_back(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
1801  }
1802  catch (...) {

1805  this->remove_front_bucket();
1806  throw;
1807  }
1808  if (StoreBackValues) {
1809  d_buckets[0].update();
1810  d_buckets[1].update();
1811  }
1812  }
1813  else {
1814  //we are going to loose value at index 0, save it
1815  std::int64_t bindex = bucket_index;
1816  //T tmp = std::move((*bucket(bindex))[0]);
1817  //bucket(bucket_index)->insert<false>(index, value);
1818 
1819  // Might throw, fine
1820  T tmp = std::move(bucket(bucket_index)->insert_pop_front(get_allocator(), index, std::forward<Args>(args)...));
1821  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bucket_index].update();
1822 
1823  //propagate down to left side
1824  while (--bindex > 0) {
1825  // Might throw, fine
1826  if (BucketType::relocatable)
1827  bucket(bindex)->push_back_pop_front_relocatable(tmp);
1828  else
1829  tmp = std::move(bucket(bindex)->push_back_pop_front(std::move(tmp)));
1830  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bindex].update();
1831  }
1832  //first bucket
1833  BucketType* bucket = d_buckets.front().bucket;
1834  if (!bucket->isFull()) {
1835  // Might throw, fine
1836  bucket->push_back(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
1837  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[0].update();
1838  }
1839  else {
1840  if (BucketType::relocatable)
1841  bucket->push_back_pop_front_relocatable(tmp);
1842  else
1843  tmp = std::move(bucket->push_back_pop_front(std::move(tmp)));
1844  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[0].update();
1845  bucket = create_front_bucket();
1846  try {
1847  bucket->push_back(get_allocator(), std::move(tmp));
1848  }
1849  catch (...) {
1850  //remove front buffer
1851  this->remove_front_bucket();
1852  throw;
1853  }
1854  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[0].update();
1855  }
1856  res = &at(pos);
1857  }

1862  {

1892  if (StoreBackValues) d_buckets[bindex].update();

1927  // Insert value at a location which is not the front or back
1928  template< class... Args >
1929  auto insert_middle_fwd(size_type pos, Args&&... args) -> T *
1930  {
1931  T* res = NULL;
1932 
1933  size_t front_size = d_buckets.front()->size;
1934  size_t bucket_index = (pos + (d_bucket_size - front_size)) >> d_bucket_size_bits;
1935  int index = (pos - (pos < front_size ? 0 : front_size)) & d_bucket_size1;
1936 
1937  if (SEQ_UNLIKELY(d_buckets.size() == 1)) {
1938  res = insert_one_bucket(bucket_index, index, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1939  }
1940  else if (pos < d_size / 2) {
1941  //bucket is on the left side
1942  res = insert_left(pos, bucket_index, index, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1943  }
1944  else {
1945  //bucket is on the right side
1946  res = insert_right(pos, bucket_index, index, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1947  }
1948 
1949  d_size++;
1950  return res;
1951  }

1953  // Insert anywhere
1954  template<class... Args>
1955  auto insert(size_type pos, Args&&... args) -> T & {
1956 
1957  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(pos <= size(), "Wrong insert position");
1958 
1959  if(pos != 0 && pos != size())
1960  return *insert_middle_fwd(pos, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1961  else if (pos==0)
1962  return emplace_front(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1963  else
1964  return emplace_back(std::forward<Args>(args)...);

1992  SEQ_ASSERT_DEBUG(d_size > 0, "tiered_vector: erase element on an empty tiered_vector");

2387  d_buckets.front()->pop_front_n(get_allocator(), (detail::cbuffer_pos)(to_remove));
2388  d_size -= to_remove;
2389  }
2390  else {
2391  //remove last bucket
2392  remove_front_bucket();
2393 
2394  to_remove -= first_bucket_size;
2395  d_size -= first_bucket_size;
2396 
2397  //dealloc buckets starting to the last one
2398  while (to_remove >= (size_type)bucket_size()) {
2399  size_type s = bucket_size(0);
2400  to_remove -= s;
2401  remove_front_bucket();
2402  d_size -= s;
2403  }
2404 
2405  //resize front bucket
2406  d_buckets.front()->pop_front_n(get_allocator(), (detail::cbuffer_pos)(to_remove));
2407  d_size -= to_remove;
2408  }
2409  }
2410  update_all_back_values();
2411  }
2412 
2413  };

3484  template<class U, class Less = std::less<T> >
3485  auto lower_bound( const U & value, const Less & le = Less()) const noexcept -> size_t
3486  {
3487  if (!d_manager)
3488  return 0;
3489  // Inspired by https://academy.realm.io/posts/how-we-beat-cpp-stl-binary-search/
3490 
3491  using BucketVector = typename bucket_manager::BucketVector;
3492  //using BucketType = typename BucketVector::value_type;
3493  const BucketVector & buckets = manager()->buckets();
3494 
3495  //find bucket
3496  using bucket_pos_type = size_t;
3497 
3498  bucket_pos_type low = 0;
3499  bucket_pos_type size = buckets.size();
3500 
3501  while ((size > (size_t)16)) {
3502  bucket_pos_type half = size / (bucket_pos_type)2;
3503  bucket_pos_type other_half = size - half;
3504  bucket_pos_type probe = low + half;
3505  bucket_pos_type other_low = low + other_half;
3506  size = half;
3507  low = le(buckets[probe].back() , value) ? other_low : low;
3508 
3509  half = size / (bucket_pos_type)2;
3510  other_half = size - half;
3511  probe = low + half;
3512  other_low = low + other_half;
3513  size = half;
3514  low = le(buckets[probe].back(), value) ? other_low : low;
3515  }
3516  size += low ;
3517  while (low < size && le(buckets[low].back(), value))
3518  ++low;
3519 
3520 
3521  if(SEQ_UNLIKELY(low == buckets.size()))
3522  return this->size();
3523 
3524  //find inside bucket
3525  bucket_pos_type b_index = low;
3526  auto * bucket = buckets[low].bucket;
3527  {
3528  using pos_type = int;//detail::cbuffer_pos
3529  pos_type size = bucket->size;
3530  pos_type low = 0;
3531 
3532  while ((size > 16) ) {
3533  pos_type half = size / 2;
3534  pos_type other_half = size - half;
3535  pos_type probe = low + half;
3536  pos_type other_low = low + other_half;
3537  size = half;
3538  low = le((*bucket)[probe], value) ? other_low : low;
3539 
3540  half = size / 2;
3541  other_half = size - half;
3542  probe = low + half;
3543  other_low = low + other_half;
3544  size = half;
3545  low = le((*bucket)[probe], value) ? other_low : low;
3546  }
3547  size += low;
3548  while (low < size && le((*bucket)[low], value))
3549  ++low;
3550 
3551 
3552  return (size_t)low + (b_index != 0 ? (size_t)buckets[0]->size + (size_t)(b_index - 1) * (size_t)(bucket)->max_size_ : (size_t)0);
3553  }
3554  }
